Would you bleed for me?
Lick it off my lips like you needed me?
Would you sit me on the couch with your fingers in my mouth?
You look so cool when your reading me.
Let’s cause a little trouble, you make me feel so weak.
I bet you kissed your knuckles right before they touch me cheek.
Today is a very hard day for me guys so please no negativity I really don’t need it and you will be instantly blocked.

Well today I had a miscarriage, I didn’t even know I was pregnant 4-5 weeks, I mean idk how to feel about it honestly me and my boyfriend and talked and agreed if I got pregnant that we would get an abortion but I didn’t get a choice in the situation, the choice got taken away from and that makes me feel some type of way, I started bleeding yesterday and thought it was my period and that I was just late at 9 pm and then had a hella bad headache come on so I went to sleep at 11 I woke up at 3 in tears with pain (I have endo, and cysts on my overies and my cysts rupture from time to time I thought it was just that mixed with the endo and period cramps) and the pain was terrible had me in tears from 3am to 9 am this morning then about 1 pm I went to the bathroom and had noticed something more than blood I called my mom and godmom and they both told me and knew as soon as I showed them that I had a miscarriage so yeah that was experience to have today, my worry the most is that because of my combo of scarring, endo, and cysts on my overies only being 19 that I don’t think I’ll be able to have kids in the future and that’s what kinda is getting to me my grandmother had all the same problems by the time she was 30 she had to get a hysterectomy and I feel like docs are gonna want me to one before I’m 30 so ugh just a lot going through my head rn
Will be more active on my DM’s now. Feel free to drop me a message 🖤
Let it make you, or break you 💪🏻

I was just watching a video of this girl wearing those super cute sweater that said “have a purpose” well at least that’s all I could read. So I looked it up and stumbled upon the shirt but something even better. I found a non profit organization called “Buddy Project”. They aim to prevent suicide by pairing people up to raise awareness about mental health. This almost made me cry. This is NOT paid. This company has no idea this account exists. I literally found this on a site called “bonfire” 10 minutes ago. I’m a seriously strong believer that a way to raise your self confidence is by writing yourself notes on the mirror everyday or having a positive quote as a phone wallpaper and definitely by wearing it!!! You guys needed to know of this incredible organization. If Orion was still alive this would have been his first Christmas present. They have many more designs than this but you have to check them out. LINK IN BIO!!!! This picture shows exactly what it’s like to live with a mental illness: you can do ”nothing” and feel completely exhausted... exhausted from:
- Fighting a war in your head 24/7
- Feeling misunderstood and alone
- Constantly having to cope with complex symptoms that are difficult to control
- Pretending to be okay so you don’t “burden” those around you
- Dealing with anxieties based on past event, present struggles, and future uncertainties - Having to justify how unwell you are because you have an invisible illness
☝️this isn’t nothing - you’re coping, you’re fighting, you’re still here. Be proud of yourself

I had a conversation with a friend recently where she explained that whenever her boyfriend noticed she was upset he’d ask her “What’s wrong?” or “Are you ok?”. She’d answer “I’m fine” as most people would when asked. And the conversation would end there. She felt like she couldn’t fully get vulnerable based off that question. It got me thinking how important the questions we ask one another are- especially when trying to get to the bottom of how someone we love is feeling.

So instead in my own life I’ve tried replacing those questions with: “What are you feeling in this current moment ?” Or “How are you, really?” These questions have been a good tool to spark better communication when I or someone I love isn’t feeling “okay.” ❣️What are some of your favorite questions to ask/ be asked when you’re feeling down? -

💊Some of us on the SGC team take meds every day, some of us have never tried them, and some of them have had negative reactions and stopped using them. Meds work differently for everyone. 💊 We have a lot of questions in our DM's about SSRIs (Selective serotonin reuptake inhibitor, also known as anti-depressants🔅), and while you should ‼️always consult a medical professional for advice‼️, we know word of mouth can help as a jump-off point. Do you take meds? What's one thing you wish you knew beforehand, and what's your experience been like since?⤵️
I'll start: Hi, I'm Em, and I used to be on Zoloft, then I took Zoloft and Wellbutrin for a while, and now I only take Wellbutrin. Zoloft helped me through two years of being in an environment that caused a lot of panic attacks and made me severely depressed. I totally wish I had known that it would give me a bit of a lower sex drive, as many SSRIs do, and that you need to take a GENEROUS sip of water beforehand or your throat will burn for the next couple hours. 🚰Wellbutrin has less side effects, but both have lowered the intensities of my anxiety-induced highs and depressive lows and made it so I could function significantly better.
Now you share yours! 🎤

•At the beginning of this year I was finally able to do what I want and become who I am, but you think being in a community is fun well it's not,  all these false accusations drama rumors,ect ect has drained my from my happiness in the scene, there are so many people who have been hurt but won’t admit what happened, all of my old friends(not gonna say names) have done a lot of tragic things and made me realize that I was gonna be in a bad situation about their own business; I tried to help them but some of them took my advice and moved on and some just stayed in the past, I hid all my sadness because I didn’t want them to see me depressed or angry for their issues, now I left all of them because it was the right thing to do, I know they will be posting about false accusations of me and that is not okay, why would you want to make fake news to people and say I’m a horrible person I’m not a bad man I’m someone who escaped from the past and moved on, so the point about this post is about moving on from the negative people and environment, trust me you’ll feel like you woke up all happiness and joy! If you know that if someone is going through what I went through please reach out to them and give them sympathy, I promise you will feel good about reaching to those people because they are trapped in a coma of agony because what they went/going through thank you for taking your time to read this I hope all of you guys are doing well and wish you the best!!

Hi friends.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I appreciate you letting me take some time away from this space. I can’t say I’m completely ready to jump back in but I can feel the gravitational pull to dip my feet back in the water I adore so much.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
The last few months I have been settling into a new job. After quitting my job in healthcare last March and attempting to make this account my full-time career to then deciding my soul didn’t want that either 🤷🏼‍♀️ to now being back to working full-time again...my brain needed quiet. I needed to simplify my outgoing current. It’s been such a whirlwind of a year and I’m learning that it’s okay to step back from some things in order to steady the ground beneath me. There were many times I came to this account but my thoughts went blank. I had nothing to say. Nothing to share. My creativity switch turned to power-saving mode and sometimes it frustrated me but I also understood. It’s okay for me to lean away from some things so I can better lean into others. A lot of my heart and energy pours into this space and I needed all the heart and energy I could muster to get me through this new transition. It’s easy for some people to start something new and still juggle the other moving parts in their life but not for me. Something always has to give, even if it’s just for a little awhile. So thank you for letting me do that.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
From a mental health standpoint, I’m doing well. I’m seeing my OCD specialist two times a month and continuing to see improvements in areas I never thought I would. There are still hard moments. There are still days when my brain plays tricks on me and my thoughts try to change the truthful narrative. But there are more good days now. So many more. This time last year I sat in my car thinking about ending my life because my OCD was so unmanageable. Here I am a year later lying in the grass outside the local farmers market, munching on some fresh cherries, writing for the first time in months, less than a week away from my 29th birthday, having the most amazing time planning our wedding and in good mental health. I am so thankful for all of that & I’m thankful for all of you.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Catch me up. How are you?💚

Thank you for participating!*** This #MentalHealthAwarenessMonth I’m excited to announce I’ve once again partnered with the hearts behind @myintent for a another MINDFUL GIVEAWAY!  @myintent is an amazing company focused on starting meaningful conversations beginning with your own customized pieces. The importance of conversation when it comes to mental health is so crucial and this is such a beautiful way to spark one.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I chose the number 9. Because on my hardest days, the I-can’t-help-but-believe-my-thoughts-even-though-I-know-it’s-my-OCD-making-something-out-of-nothing-days, or the painful and empty days- I want to remember my favorite month with my favorite person. I want to remember the love, the support, and the blanket of happiness that wraps itself around me whenever I think of the month of September- our dating month, our engagement month and our future wedding month. When I look down I remember the journey I’m never walking alone and how grateful I am for this amazing man who loves even the darkest parts of me. That is why I chose 9.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

This time last year I quit my full-time career to take the biggest risk of my life. By March 2018 I had been managing this account for 6 years. I never made a penny from it before then. People would say “Wow you could be making so much money! Why don’t you do sponsored content?! I know this person and they made thousands off of just one post!” Honestly, those suggestions always frustrated me. I wasn’t in it for that. I created this community from the ground up because it’s what I needed during the loneliest season of my life. There’s no dollar amount that could have given me the comfort and support like I’ve found here. I didn’t want to capitalize off this safe place and be another person trying to market the latest fit tea or hair gummy in exchange for a check. I wouldn’t do it.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I was working in healthcare at that time. I loved the work I did but I hated the cost of doing it. I was barely making ends meet, had a growing credit card bill, immersed in toxic management and I was so fucking tired. Careful deliberation mixed with pure exhaustion and I made the decision that if I was going to make this account my career it had to be done my way. I had to create my own box for me to fit into. Mindful partnerships. Relevant sponsored ads. Complete and total transparency. It took hours of therapy for me to reframe my mindset and accept that I was worthy of financially supporting myself while also doing what I love. I’ve never had both before. It’s always been one or the other and the idea that I could possibly live a comfortable life while loving what I did seemed like a path worth exploring. So I quit. I took the biggest risk of my life and I quit to pursue that full-time influencer life but on my terms.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
And guess what?
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I couldn’t do it.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I’m just not built for it.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
My storytelling doesn’t work this way.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
More to come on why I’m going back to work. More to come on why it’s okay to admit “I CAN’T DO SOMETHING BECAUSE I’M HUMAN AND I CAN’T DO SOME SHIT!” So this risk didn’t make for a great success story in the end. Ah well. What matters is that I learned and maybe that’s the ending I was always meant for.
Oh my. @risingwoman

These words in my post yesterday seem to have spoken to many of you so I thought I’d highlight it. When you all find comfort in my words, it lights my heart up. Thank you for your support yesterday. Here’s to being the flower, here’s to being the rain and here’s to seeing the purpose in both💚

I cried a lot today. Hard and a lot.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I felt worthless today.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I felt directionless today.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I felt hopeless today.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I felt like a failure today.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I left work early because I simply couldn’t do it today.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
There are going to be days like this. It’s okay.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I picked up my favorite food on my way home, put on a show that makes me forget about my phone, lit a candle, waved around some Palo Santos 47 times because cleansing and because the energy I’m carrying sucks, cried some more and then put on this Bat Eye Mask (a clean product I got at the @credobeauty event last night) and suddenly I felt like I had no place at my dining room table anymore but instead belonged on the set of the next Marvel film. I don’t know what this mask is doing but I’m on board. Life is weird sometimes. There’s so much going on. So many questions and decisions. So much to know. So much I don’t. Honesty, I’m not sure I know what the fuck I’m doing sometimes. Sometimes I lose sight of my place and my purpose. Sometimes, not always, I believe I don’t know a damn thing about a damn thing. Some days I forget who I am and the places I’m worthy of going. These days happen. These thought patterns happen. Sometimes your inner critic speaks louder than your inner supporter. These days don’t decide tomorrow.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Some days I’m the flower and other days I’m the rain. Today I’m the latter and although it’s unpleasant and it hurts and it’s uncomfortable, I know the purpose I’m serving. I know the growth I’m igniting. I know the flowers that need me. I know that taking a mental health day has never failed me. I also know I’ll be going back for another one of these masks.

When @blofishclothing asked me which coordinates I wanted I pictured myself on April 5, 2013 walking up to an old friend I hadn’t seen in years. I remember us standing outside of the restaurant where he was waiting tables, both of us smiling bigger than we could conceal. “So are you seeing anyone?” I couldn’t believe I had asked that within 45 seconds of catching up. Ballsy. Maybe it was the fresh ink tingling under the bandage on my arm, maybe it was because that wild serendipitous chain of events brought out the bold in me, or maybe it was because I just knew. And after we hugged goodbye and I received a text from him moments later simply saying “😊” I don’t think I was the only one. So this string of numbers will always be that special place to me- the place that I ran into an old friend. And now this tee is the perfect comfy shirt to wear on the couch while we plan our wedding.

One of the best decisions I have made recently for my mental health- KICKING COFFEE. I went from drinking two (sometimes three) cups a day to a half a cup a week. And pretty soon even that won’t be the case. What was once a nostalgic, creamy, cozy favorite part of my morning is now an undeniable trigger for my OCD and anxiety. Holy shit. I didn’t see it before. Kinda hard to notice the absence of something that I was never without, but once I noticed how quiet my brain became, how easily it was for me to manage my symptoms and just how overall clearheaded and great I felt, I’ll never go back🙅🏼‍♀️☕️ It was a devastating breakup. Andrew’s proposal was even purposely revolved around our morning coffee because it’s that important to us, however feeling happy and healthy trumps a past morning routine that can easily be adjusted! This is my own personal experience. If you drink coffee and feel just fine, great! If you drink coffee and notice a reactive body and mind, consider what you’re putting into it💚 I’m not caffeine-free, I’m coffee-free. I’ve just noticed I react differently to the source in which I’m getting it from. These @myteadrop came with my @thebrogliebox! They’re like little tea bathbombs for my boiling water and I love them! So here’s a tea toast to my new found love for tea and how quickly it filled that void for me!🍵

Let’s talk fear of panic attacks in public or for some of you panic attacks TRIGGERED by public. 
I personally struggled with both in the past. 
I always had a fear of “embarrassing” myself by having a panic attack in public. I could even visualize it and of course my visualizations were always 100 times more dramatic than the situation would/could ever be. I imagined not being able to control myself, freaking out, and an ambulance having to take me to the doctor... needless to say as much as I feared this, it never happened. That’s my biggest point today- almost all of our fears, biggest worries never come true or even close to true but we spend so much time thinking about them, playing them out like they exist and almost acting like it already happened sometimes. Comment 🙋🏼‍♀️ if you can relate to that one. 
Then there is panic triggered by public. If you are anything like me you have created a correlation (That isn’t true but youve convinced yourself it is) that going in public or to certain places will automatically cause a panic attack. I know I am very guilty of this. I let it get to the point of everywhere I had had a panic attack or felt my heart racing before I cut off ever going back to... which led to agoraphobia. I made a connection in my brain that being home was only safe. I wish someone would’ve looked at me back then and said walk back into that store and don’t leave- show yourself and your mind that that store isn’t dangerous and the panic attack wasn’t caused by the store it was caused by the fear and anxious thoughts I had leading up to the store. That’s when I started exposure therapy with myself- showing my mind that the places I “feared” going to due to having a past panic attack weren’t dangerous but I related them to the panic attack and labeled them as dangerous. Showing myself and my mind that I can go there and be okay helped lessen the fear, which helped lessen the thoughts. If we constantly go into a situation with the mindset “this makes me anxious, i am worried about having a panic attack there because this this and this” then we are ultimately setting ourselves up to panic. “I am” two of the most powerful words known. I don’t care if you don’t feel it, claim it. It’s easy to say “I am depressed I am anxious” but we are subconsciously setting the tone for our mental state. You have the power. You set the tone to what you want to be today. “Today, I am brave and any anxiety that comes my way might be irritating but that’s okay because I am brave and it will pass”
I used to think it was dumb to claim stuff like that... until I read the science behind it. Why we might think it’s dumb but when you continually claim things you start to believe them..then you start to feel them. This is true science.
I’m guilty of in the past being the ultimate negative Nancy 🙋🏼‍♀️🙋🏼‍♀️
Things I used to say “I am not smart enough” “I am too anxious””I am depressed” “ I am not enough” “I am not okay” and feeding my brain that over & over took a toll.
Even when I don’t feel okay, I remind myself I am okay. 
Even when I don’t feel like I’m enough, I remind myself I am enough & capable of all things.
You are too.
So today, what are you?

Intrusive thoughts by definition are unwanted thoughts or images that you find distressing. These unwanted thoughts are known as obsessions. What gives these thoughts power is when people who experience them become worried about the significance of the thoughts. Reminder: thoughts are just thoughts, they are not real nor harmful. 
Some examples of intrusive thoughts:
1. “I always feel like everyone is looking at me and laughing. If someone is laughing it has to be at me. If people are taking it’s about me”
2. “I truly feel something terrible is about to happen any second” and then possibly seeing the scenario in your head of what you are worried about. 
3. “I don’t really love my significant other” When they are the most important person in your life.
4. “My children would be better off with a better mom. My husband only stays with me because I’m free day care. No on loves me.” These are just some.. then there are other deeper intrusive thoughts that you may be dealing with- thoughts of doing something impulsive. *TRIGGER WARNING*
In the past during my panic disorder I had the same intrusive thought come to my mind a few times while driving, it was when I was driving over a bridge “what if I just drove off the ledge” It wasn’t an action thought but it was the most random thought that would appear and scare me. Back then before I knew how to cope with thoughts, I feared the thought was bigger than me and would cause me to do that. But the truth is thoughts are just thoughts and WE have the power. 
If you experience intrusive thoughts, trust me I know its scary. I remember when I would get those thoughts I would feel “bad” for thinking that. But what I did to help was remind myself that it was just a thought, a thought cannot hurt me, a thought is an imagination not a real action. I have the power to not act on my thoughts. 
Continually going through the process in your mind when you get the these unwanted thoughts. 
Steps to take to deal with intrusive thoughts: 
1. Label your intrusive thoughts as “just thoughts” Remind yourself they have no power.
2. Remind yourself that you have the power and you can safely avoid them

If you look you might see the timeline of my life a little different than it was.
I look happy in the black dress, but I was deep in perfectionism, needing to be accepted, needing to fit in. I always had to look perfect, be perfect, act perfect. Was happy on the outside but on the inside was destroying myself. Running miles and miles daily and eating little to nothing to make sure I stay in the “best shape”, even choosing my major in nutrition and dietetics to make sure I always stay “perfect” with my boyfriend and outward appearance..
None of that led to happiness, I always ended up being around people I wasn’t, being someone I wasn’t. I was never fully fulfilled.
Then the next picture- in the deepest of my panic disorder. I had anxiety my whole life but then I randomly got hit with extreme panic disorder in college when my body said ENOUGH. I wouldn’t slow down and take care of myself and my mental health that my body decided to show me some payback.
The panic attacks were many a day, the symptoms were debilitating, I didn’t see a life without it in the future. The depression was dark. I didn’t care to get better because I felt hopeless. I didn’t think recovery was ever possible. I thought my “perfect” life was over and this is what I was left with- me, my bed, google, and the constant fear that I was dying.
Then one day enough became enough. I wasn’t trying to get better I was just expecting to randomly wake up and the panic be gone.
Then I made changes in my life, I put recovery first. I won’t sit here and say it was easy and so simple. It was freaking hard. But nothing changes if nothing changes.
Here I am, this last picture. This week I just hit 100,000 followers and have the honor to help & guide 100,000 to hope & recovery. I was chosen as a finalist by WEGO health @wegohealth  awards for best in show instagram. I found that everything was meant to be. The reason I majored in nutrition & dietetics was disorderedly in the moment, but now I get to use it for good helping people heal their guts and gain mental clarity since mental health & nutrition go hand in hand. It’s easy to feel alone in a world of social media where only the “happy times” are posted.

You’re not alone.

Today, might be a hard day for some of you. 18 years ago America was under attack on 9/11/2001. In the moment everyone’s world felt scared and like it was falling apart. We lost many beautiful humans that day. It is easy to say why did they deserve this? Why did it happen? I asked these same questions a lot when I was working in the children’s hospital… I would look at this most perfect little baby… fighting to live. Why them? They have only gotten to see this world for just a second, don’t they deserve more time? I met a family, who had recently lost their child after birth. The mom was admirable. She had started a foundation for parents struggling & through that foundation she helped thousands. She told me something I will never forget “though in the moment of losing my beautiful baby, I found peace in knowing that she did more for my life & a lifetime with her would have done” I was forever inspired by strength. I thought today while we remember 9/11, we speak about the people who have made beauty from ashes and helped so many around the world with their story and experience. 
1. Michael Lynch was one of the firefighters who lost their lives on 9/11. His family and friends created the Michael Lynch Memorial Foundation in his honor. So far the foundation has raised more than $3.5 million in college scholarships. 
2.  Jay Winuk’s younger brother helped evacuate his law office on 9/11 and then ran into the other tower to help try to rescue people, losing his own life in the process. Alot of my clients ask how do they stop the negative thoughts they are getting, the key to breaking the negative cycle of thinking and anxiety is to Change your relationship with your thoughts. Allow the thoughts to come and almost be a bystander and question the validity of the thoughts you are thinking. Thoughts are not facts they are random messed up information and are well known for being aload of BS. By changing the way you react to your thoughts you are teaching your brain that there is an alternative way of thinking and instead of seeing the negative thoughts as a threat or danger your brain will dismiss the thoughts almost immediately.
-
-Journalling is a great way to start to put this into practice next time you recognise a negative thought write it down and next to it write down an alternative positive thought. This is giving your brain the alternative outlook practice practice practice until it becomes second nature and you are not having to write the thoughts down you will get to the stage where you are doing it subconsciously. 💕💕💕

ANXIETY
It's a stress response, a natural human mechanism that is here to sense danger, real or perceived. When it senses danger, from mesages like for example, worry or high tension it sends a message to your adrenal gland to start the stress hormones pumping through your body.
If you were in an actual in front of your eyes danger like about to fall of a cliff, it would kick in to give you that quick assessment & boost of adrenaline to escape. Then the symptoms of adrenaline would feel normal. You wouldn't question that human reaction.
.
But because the danger is unseen & gradual.
Too much worry 
Life problems for a while 
Fearful
Hormones imbalance
Too much doing all the time, no break mental or physical.
Not enough nutrician leading to a lack of vitamin or mineral in the body causing stress on the body.
A closed mindset
Feeling inferior all the time
Etc. Etc.
.
Now this danger on the mind & body we question the symptoms.
.
Why am I anxious?
This isn't normal
These symptoms feel like there's something else badly working.
I'm scared all the time
I'm broken
Etc.
.
❤Darling you are not, if you don't look after yourself physically & mentally allow yourself to take a break, put a break in your planning daily. Your mind & body will tell you, It's sensing danger to your health.
.
👋HI you in charge of us, we are in need of calm, of a break, of a mental declutter, of nutrician, of distressing,  of a check up at the docs, of a bit of self love. If we don't we will get Ill, this is dangerous to us. So I've sensed the danger & stress response is on, show us that calm is possible, that you can calm & recover & I will switch it off. Love amygdala. ❤
.
Start listening to your needs, no more 🚫'Must keep going'
.
Put in actionable plans to make your human needs a daily priority.
.
That's you working together for better health. Mind & body harmony 🤝
.

📈ANXIETY
A natural human response to STRESS in the mind or body. Perceived or real DANGER.
Such as
An existing illness, WORRYING you & putting STRAIN on your body. 
Too much WORRY in your life
HOLDING in intense EMOTION, swallowing it. 
HORMONE imbalance
NO sleep
NO support 
Loneliness, sadness.
Not enough NUTRITIONAL value in your diet
A LACK of magnesium
PAIN from the past that hasn't gone anywhere.
A CLOSED MINDSET
FEAR of something 
Etc.
.
📈What happens is we experience anxiety because of a cause such as 1 or many of the above, & without knowledge of anxiety, & not knowing about the real causes, we become fearful of anxiety. Then we beat ourselves up for experiencing it, assume it's down to us as a human that were some how broken. The worry continues, causing more anxiety.
.
💡It's not as you imagine.
Experiencing anxiety can be helped, be brought down, you can feel better again. So that the next time you experience anxiety from one of the above causes *life* *anxiety is normal for the circumstances* you will know how to manage it, you won't feel afraid & you'll know how to bring it down= less worry, passes sooner. Then 👇
Address the causes.
.
BUT
.
❤The 1st move is to take care of your Heart
No more blaming yourself
Accepting you're feeling anxious 
It WILL pass
But you Have to take care
You cannot expect anxiety to reduce doing  all the same things as before. The things that caused anxiety.
.
📉A better sleep routine 
Ask for support
A nutritional diet 
Cancel plans
Breathe
Don't plan too much
Productivity 👎not important, your health & wellbeing is.
Have some nights in
Put down social media
Do something you enjoy
Get outside 🌳🕊
Speak to a doctor
Know that you deserve to feel good even if you're not used to putting you first, it's time you did. Waiting for that person to do it, will probubly never happen. You do it for you. Put your arms around yourself, make a promise to yourself that you are strong enough to love you like you should be loved.
.
Take care x
.

A counsellor
.
🌸Places I felt comfortable chatting, swapping a bit of my life story & feeling comfortable doing it.
.
BUT not before I'd seen the cbt therapist i visited when I was experiencing fear of going out, fear of sleeping, fear or eating, fear fear fear which turned out to be fear of panic happening anywhere.
.
🗣She asked me how are you? It was the first time I felt that I could REALLY answer that question honestly. .
No-one was going to get upset with my words. 
No-one would find out how I really felt.
No-one had ever really truely wanted to know, really!
I had never felt that I could have a connection like that with anyone.
.
Boy did I cry, i cried for the whole hour, 'someone is asking me for real how am I?'
It was an hour well spent, the best I ever had because I connected with someone.
.
The connection had been missing.
TRUSTING someone, to just listen, let me be honest without making what I said about them. Trusting someone would want to listen, that I was safe to say.
.
That was my true healing, what I needed the most.
The rest came from knowledge of anxiety & trusting that they wanted to help me. Talking helped me to unravel all that was going on in my mind, from one ball of mess which was fear of anxiety, fear of emotion, pain from the past, not looking after myself, my needs, my heart. Coping mechanisms that didnt serve me well now, family patterns i had learnt. Plus all the problems that were in my life then. All together, with no trust & no help was unorganized & unmanageable 😓
.
So if you are thinking about therapy or you have connected to my story.
You deserve that feeling you can trust someone, it's what you should have. If you haven't had it, just like me you can look for it until you find it, from the doctor, from a therapist, from a coach.
.
You don't have to wait for them to change, you can make a change.
.
#anxiety #trust

MORE 
You've done your work but still feel that its not enough, you must give more.

You've earned enough for what you NEED but in your thoughts it's not enough.
.
You're always spending, then next thing comes up that you want, the 😊 didn't last long. What's next?
.
You feel you must own more, what you have isn't enough.
.
I should be feeling more, happy, I'm always questioning 'am I happy enough?'
.
🤔That's just an idea/belief we've been feed to keep the commercial world earning 💰you think you NEED it. You've done your best but still, it doesn't feel enough. .
WHY?
.
Do you know about the ABC model? Ellis.
.
Actionable event 
Beliefs 
Concequenses.
.
Most people think that cognitively 
we go A-C👇
Event- it makes us feel a certain way so we - act. 👇
You pass someone in the street, they appear to ignore you(A)- you feel angry or upset so you decide to ignore them next time. (C)
.
But. Really it's A-B-C example👇
.
You pass someone in the street, they appear to ignore you(A)- you feel angry or upset (subconcious memory) you believe that they must be ignoring you because this isn't the first time someone has appeard to ignore you (B) so you decide to ignore them next time.(C)
.
So how does that come into play in this scenario of MORE? 
If we have been feed ideas that we never have enough & this idea is a pretty lucrative one if you are selling a product that you want people to want. So how do you do it?
.
Advertise it like you need it!!
.
It's psychology, & the commercial world has been telling you you need IT since adverts began.
.
It's now part of our subconcious So.
.
You work (A) you feel tired & in need of a break but you believe it's not enough, we have to keep striving for more(B)you keep going even though it's not good for you(C)
.

Change your belief=change the action

A-ANXIOUS

A complete mix of emotions vs a straight line, you wouldn't feel anything.
.
✒@anxiety_wellbeing
🎨@thepsychologymum 🌱
.
🌱Anxiety 
It's one of the emotions that is very tough to deal with, mainly because if you become afraid of how you feel *normal* then it becomes something you try to avoid, block, run from & that, makes you feel worse.
.
🌱*Its normal that when you first experience high anxiety, panic attacks, or sometimes even suspect that you're anxious, that you will start to worry. & that's because.
.
1. Many of the symptoms feel like there IS something else badly wrong.
2. When we experience panic, this alone is very scary so fear & anxiety go hand in hand.
3. In stress response the brain naturally scans for danger, so if you feel & feel the fear it's normal.
4. If you have no knowledge, this can lead to assuming the worst. =more anxiety
5. We are talking about mental health so much, when you do feel down, now we are focused inward thinking 'is there something wrong with me have I got it?'.
.
🌱As much as emotions are tough to deal with they are tougher if you question their existence & become afraid of them.
.
🌱When we do this we block, avoid the real emotion that actually should be experienced & allowed to flow through you in its own way.
.
🌱Emotion doesn't go if you swallow, block or avoid, they stay with you, build up, come out in other ways. In behaviour, I'm health. Sometimes with anxiety.
.
🌱It can feel incredibly uncomfortable to feel an emotion but it's not hear to hurt you, you have reason to feel the way you feel, of you allow yourself to feel it, it will pass, you will feel better, it may take time but it will pass.
.
🌱No feelings, no emotions, what would that mean?
If you're never been heart broken you never LOVED
If you're you're never sad, you won't APPRECIATE GLADNESS.
If you're never anxious, you're survival mechanism isn't serving you well.
If you're never anything, you're feeling numb.
.
🌱Emotions are here to help us navigate our world's, feel all the feels, let them out, enjoy humaness. 😍
.

THE MOMENT YOU ASK YOURSELF TO STOP THINKING ABOUT SOMETHING | This command is a direct sure fire way you will be more focused on it | There is a way👇
.
.✒@anxiety_wellbeing 🎨@who knows the artist?
.
HOW?
HOW is it that you are asking yourself to stop thinking about it, you don't want to be thinking about it BUT it's now the only thing you're thinking about.
*any thought you are not comfortable with.
.
AMYGDALA
The part of the brain that senses danger, starts the fight flight freeze response, anxiety. This comes on because it's sensed a danger perceived or real, it sends a message to your adrenal glands for stress hormones, you feel edgy, the adrenalin is on. Your amygdala also needs to continue scanning for danger. To judge if the danger is over.
.
'Are we safe yet? not sure so I will keep focused for negative/danger.'
.
This is a natural human response that has helped to keep the humam race alive all this time. We need it, it's doing a good job. If we are overly stressed with worries, & our bodies are not getting what it needs this can be a cause for anxiety, rightly so, we won't be doing well if we are compromising the mind & body. This is a danger to your health & wellbeing.
.
So most of us are operating at a level of stress & not really eating well for ourselves. We can help that by reducing stress, eating a balanced diet.
.
THE THOUGHTS!
When you ask yourself to stop thinking of something. It's a signal to the brain that reads a bit like this.
.
🤔: Stop thinking that!
.
AMYGDALA: What thought where? this must be dangerous it's not nice, I sense this isn't good, keep scanning for danger we might not be ok here.'
.
😣:I can't stop thinking about this, now I'm feeling worried, maybe even scared, why can't I stop?
.
AMYGDALA:I sense fear, this isn't good, keep scanning!. Don't stand down yet!.
.
SO WHAT CAN YOU DO?
.
🤔: I've noticed I'm thinking something that I don't like, I acknowledge it's there & let it pass, I'll distract my thoughts with, a nice memory, music I enjoy, a funny sketch, an activity I enjoy.etc
.
AMYGDALA :nothing to see here we're calm, I sense no fear, gently stand down.
.
🙄: Distracted, thought comes, goes. Then I forget.
.
#anxiety

GRATEFUL | ESPECIALLY TODAY. LIFE HAPPENS AND YOU REALISE HOW SPECIAL EVERY MOMENT IS.
.
Trust me everyday is a good day when you experience a day when it really means that.
.
✒@anxiety_wellbeing .
🎨@stacieswift 🌱🌱
.
Here I am sitting in the recovery room with my son. LIFE was just going along as normal.
Up, breakfast 
School
Work
Shopping 
Drive here and there
Thinking 'Oh I need a break'.
'Wow I'm tired'
'I wish it was more autumny'
'I wish this that and the other'.
You know all those thoughts that cross your mind.
.
And yet last night we went to a & e with my son not knowing he had a burst appendix, wishing to be home an comfy and not in the waiting room.
.
But how grateful are we.
We were in the right place 
We were with the right people
Life is an absolute gift. 
One minute all the daily stuff is getting you down. The next you do nothing but wish everything was back to normal.
.
I'm grateful to the surgeon who worked late to save my boy, all the staff here, everyone around me. Friends family. My son for such bravery 
And for life today. Present loving every breath.
.
Give yourself a little reminder of how wonderful the everyday really is. ❤
.

'can not leave the rat race!'.
.

.

SOMETIMES THE REASON IS BECAUSE YOU DON'T KNOW WHY? So we go no further on the subject. Learn why?👇
.
✒@anxiety_wellbeing
🎨@crazyheadcomics 🙎🏻‍♀️
.
😑SAYING YES!.
Can be stressfull, can cause you anxiety, because what you really need to do is say no, but instead you don't know how or why you've said yes but you've said it. Makes it even harder to back down now, so you feel obliged to continue.
.
Constantly feeling that you've compromised yourself will bring your confidence down, dull your emotions, cause you anxiety. Because "Why do I keep saying yes, I don't actually want to do that thing or see that person.'
.
👇
Why do we?
Because we're worried about the reaction
Worried about HOW to say no!
Worried we are letting someone down.
Worried it feels strange & new to say no, you're not used to it?
Maybe you've learnt from childhood, maybe you have been In situations where it wasn't safe to say no, where you felt entirely obliged to put someone else first or else! 
Fearful of what will happen.
.
This is all a normal way of coping in a situation, we go through experiences along the way in life & learn coping skills that we feel are appropriate at the time BUT they may not be appropriate now, maybe a coping mechanism is holding you back, is fear based, you can change.
.
If you want to say no!
You want to cancel
Change your mind
Put yourself first
.
You can
You don't have to do it in a way that's going to offend.
You are in charge of you.
You can decide 
There's no need to be defending yourself
.
🤔WHEN 
something is coming up & you want to say no thanks. 
STOP for a minute 
Is this something you want to do?
👉If Yes, are you afraid of something. Try not to let fear stop you doing someting you want to Do! Emotions pass, get comfortable with feeling a little nervous, try not to let that stop you it will pass.
👉If no, say no, kindly but firmly. You may get people saying 'oh come on' because there not used to you saying no, or they want you to, for them. 
Stay kind but firm.
No thankyou.
.
It's new, it feels strange, you're learning a new way that's helpful to you. You can decide what you need. 🤗
.

MENTAL ENERGY WHERE IS YOURS GOING? | Try not to fall into the trap?! What trap? 👇👇
.
✒@anxiety_wellbeing
🎨@kaha.mind 🌱
.
When we think about our energy, I think it's normal that we connect with our physical energy & what we are DOING. We can see that if you are doing something like working a 9-5 then you can picture where your energy is going but, mental energy is a bit of another conversation & not so easy to spot if you're not sure.
.
ENERGY TRAPS
Where is your mental energy going?
🤦‍♀️If you wake up thinking about the dreaded day ahead. Do you enjoy your present morning before you start?
🤦‍♂️If you have an appointment that you are worried about, are you placing your mind at the appointment before you're even there, spending the time worrying about it, when actually the appointment lasts 30 mins with worry time lasting 2 weeks 22hs
🤦‍♀️If you have experienced anxiety are you constantly focused on body sensations placing your entire day around "could I be getting anxious now?".
🤦‍♂️Are you in a relationship where they need help, but don't actually help themselves. You worry on their behalf all the time and make all the effort, hoping they will change. Where's all you mental energy going? Do you have time to think about yourself?
.
You mental energy is not best spent worrying or worrying for someone else & it's hard to let go of that worry, we get that instant feeling of dred when we contemplate letting go "What will happen?
.
Nothing will happen, nothing changes that isn't in your control.
.
Worrying doesn't make change.
Actions do
Worrying steals present peace
Worrying causes anxiety to increase.
Your mental energy is best spent on what you can control. 
Worrying won't change a person, they only way they'll change is if they want to.
.
LETTING GO TIPS
If you catch yourself using your mental energy worrying.
.
Stop
Take a breath
Observe the situation
Are you present of the moment or in the past or future?
Is worrying helping?
Will it change anything?
What could you do with this energy if you let go?
'I notice where my mental energy is going, it's not helping, I choose to let it go & refocus my thoughts in something helpful.
Lots. ❤
.

IS COFFEE GOOD OR BAD FOR YOU? // At last I have the answer! Is coffee good or bad for you? ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Well...
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
It depends.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
For some people, coffee doesn’t have a huge stimulating effect. Some people can sleep after a cup of coffee post-dinner (who are these people?!! 🙈) It has some benefits too - like protecting the liver.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
For others - MOST OF YOU WHO FOLLOW - it is simply anxiety fuel that you don’t need. It’s pumping stress hormones like adrenaline and cortisol into your already stressed out, over-stimulated nervous system. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Try a week or two off it. See if you notice an improvement in your anxiety and sleep. Take the Calm In 5 Days email challenge while you’re at it, for bonus support!! Link in bio❤️

MEDITATION - WHY YOU’RE NOT DOING IT PART ONE // It’s not always an easy gig getting my clients to meditate regularly. 
I work with a lot of people with anxiety. Understanding anxiety is the first step in managing it. In knowing its erratic nature, we can obtain a better sense of triggering situations and how our anxiety operates. That’s where meditation comes in. 
Whether you frequently experience that butterflies in the stomach, sweaty palms, heart palpitations, upset stomach, or tightness in the chest feeling of adrenaline pumping or not, we know there are a myriad of benefits to meditation.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
So what is stopping you from meditating?
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
There is one reason that comes up time and time again, in my client sessions and across the world.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I DON’T HAVE TIME TO MEDITATE.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Is this you? Do you think this too? ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
The problem here is that we all assume meditation has to be done in a 10, 20, 30 or 60 minute format, with certain rules. We are making it too hard for ourselves. Staying in meditation for less than 10 minutes and you’ve failed. There are no rules. 5 minutes is enough. Even 1 minute is enough! The person who watches their mind and breath for 1 minute a day is still receiving benefits over the person who never watches their mind. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Personally, I usually meditate for 5-10 minutes here and there and it’s become a really regular part of my life. I can fit it in anywhere, just before bed, after a walk or session at the gym.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
If you struggle to meditate regularly, see what happens when you take the rules away.
If you would like to work further on your anxiety, I’d love to work with you. Send me a DM and let’s talk! ❤️

GUT TROUBLES? EAT THIS 👆🏻// Anxiety and an uncomfortable digestive system often go hand in hand. Have you noticed this yourself? ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
It can make the gut spasm into diarrhoea, or stop moving completely, so we get constipation 💩 ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Many people also experience bloating, gastric acid reflux and simply just feel discomfort when digesting food! All because of high stress levels and anxiety, and how our brain and gut are connected.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
For more comfortable digestion, try adding more papaya to your diet 🌸 This is one of my go-to suggestions for my clients!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Papaya contains natural digestive enzymes that take the pressure off your body, so you can break down your food better (and more easily absorb nutrients). ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

EVER TRIED DEALING WITH ANXIETY LIKE THIS? // So when you feel anxious all you want is to NOT feel anxious. You want to stop it. You want it to end ASAP. I get it. Ooooh believe me, I know the urge to just take it away.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
But you’ve tried that, haven’t you? ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Have you ever tried something different...
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Have you ever tried just... letting it in? What if you allowed it to be there? ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

This is the easiest most nutritious cool weather breakfast... It’s like a green smoothie, but warm, doughy and crispy. These pancakes have been so popular!! A nice dose of greens, with magnesium & B vitamins for a calm nervous system. Now you can make them this weekend... 😏💚 Comment below if you’re going to make them!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
GREEN PANCAKES:⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
1 banana⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
1 egg⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
1/2 cup spinach⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
1/2 cup oats⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
1/2 tsp cinnamon⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Blend ingredients together. Pour batter into pan with coconut oil and cook both sides for 1-2 minutes of until golden.

THE LINK BETWEEN ANXIETY AND YOUR GUT // Just went LIVE 🎥 in the Anxiety Reset Community on FB talking about the gut and its interaction with the brain for building resilience to anxiety. Want to listen in full? Then find the group on Facebook and request to join us! 👏🏼
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
A major reason for digestive symptoms such as diarrhoea, or loose bowel motions, constipation, or bloating and gas, appetite changes, even food intolerances, is actually the state of your nervous system... and the balance of bacteria in your gut has an impact on your brain! You know I’ll always tell you the good 💩!!

WHAT KIND OF CLINICAL TESTING IS AVAILABLE? // Its pretty amazing what you can learn about the body from blood, saliva, stool and hair! I use various clinical lab tests where appropriate as part of The Anxiety Reset Method for my one-on-one clients, such as:
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
💩 stool testing to investigate the microbiome and nutrient absorption⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
💇‍♀️ hair mineral analysis to assess long term mineral status⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
🌸 saliva hormone testing to assess hormonal balance⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
🔬 standard blood testing analysis⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
This is how we can determine whether there are underlying physical issues influencing your anxiety - like out of balance gut bacteria, hormones or minerals.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Any testing you may require is organised online. Your test kit is sent out to you in the post. You can then submit your sample to the lab (all instructions are included in the kit) and then the results are sent back to me electronically. We can then look through your results together using screen sharing, so you can look at what’s on my screen while I’m explaining it all to you in detail. Send me a DM if you’d like to talk more about testing! ✨
You can get through this moment of anxiety 🙏 Do you find these words helpful? Share with someone you love, and sign up for Calm In 5 Days for more support (link in bio) if you haven’t yet!! 💕

WHEN DID YOU LAST GO NATURAL? // Feeling like a new human. I’m back, I’m well, there’s 10K of you now 🙈 wow! WELCOME!! And I’m embracing the natural curl. Where are my curly girls? 🙋🏽‍♀️ I challenge you to join me. Go curly today - no straightener!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
When we constantly straighten or alter our natural hair day after day, it’s a little bit like saying to yourself, “natural me isn’t good enough, I have to change it”. Right?
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Or maybe it’s the concealer you think you must wear under your eyes, the lashes, the brow kit, the fake tan. Every day. Whatever it is you do to alter your natural appearance. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Of course make up and hair-styling is fun to do! 💅🏻💇‍♀️💄
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
But I’m just saying, there’s a point we reach when we don’t feel like it’s okay to take a photo or be seen outside without it. You all know what I’m talking about 🙈 If that’s you, I want you to remember this...
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Natural you, just as you are, IS good enough, IS beautiful and one day if I have a curly-haired daughter, I’d love her to know she doesn’t have to hide her curls to feel enough.

The song playing in the background of my mind with this quote is ‪Pat Benatar‬’s “Hit Me With Your Best Shot”. 😊This mindset of “bring it on” encompasses all the messy experiences of fear, power, bravery, discomfort, anxiety, and courage.
.
.
When we find ourself standing at that proverbial fork in the road, we find ourselves with (at times) pretty tough decisions to make. In that moment, how do we engage with our experience? How do we engage with our uncertainty? How do we engage with our anxiety? One option we have is to avoid. To escape that moment of discomfort. To run from fear. To let fear choose our path for us. When this isn’t in line with our values, what do we do?
.
.
Another option is this life motto: “hey anxiety, bring it on”. I say this to myself anytime I feel that tug of fear within myself urging me to flee. I use this as a gentle and compassionate reminder that I can allow fear to be a part of my experience without needing to do something about it.
.
.
"Yes, anxiety. Yes, fear. If you want to join me in this experience then you are welcome, but you do not get a drivers seat position. You can watch me live my life according to my values and not your own. I got this.”
.
.
Reminder: You can do hard things. You can do brave things. I believe in you SO much. You got this!
.
.

We may think that just one more compulsion, just one more ritual, will be enough to satisfy OCD. OCD will then be satiated and leave us alone. The frustrating reality is that no amount of rituals will satisfy that doubt, that discomfort, that uncertainty. It may feel like it’s better momentarily, but because of the way a ritual negatively reinforces intrusive thoughts and the resulting anxiety, the cycle will happen again. The rituals are food for those experiences to get stronger and keep coming back.
.
An example of a negative reinforcement cycle: I have a headache. I feel pain and I do not want to be in pain. I then take headache medicine with the goal of getting rid of the pain. As a result of taking the medicine, the headache goes away. The behavior of taking the medicine was reinforced by the diminishment of my pain. What happens next time? I’m now more likely to have that thought of “oh I should take medicine!” the next time I have a headache and then follow through with my behavior of taking the medication.
.
Rituals function the same way. We perform them with the intention of getting rid of our anxiety/doubt/discomfort/fear. It may “work” momentarily but because of this temporary relief, that intrusion is now being reinforced as a dangerous thing that we need to ritualize around.
.
This is why ERP is so difficult. We have to sit with our anxiety and really invite it to be a part of our experience without engaging in rituals intended to take that discomfort away. Over time and consistency, that reinforcement cycle breaks apart and we can learn new things about the experience of an intrusion (thoughts are just thoughts) and anxiety (anxiety is unpleasant but not dangerous) and uncertainty (it is a part of the human experience and can be embraced). This can be so hard but it is so worth it! You are worth it!
.
I believe in your ability to do hard things! I believe in YOU! You got this💛
.

Have you ever struggled with the notion that feeling afraid must mean that you are not a strong individual? That the experience of fear removes any opportunity for strength? I believe it’s actually quite the contrary. It is a strength to be able to make values-based decisions amid feeling fear and anxiety. It is a strength to feel fear and discomfort and tolerate that experience. It is a strength to get up each day knowing there is a battle ahead (or present). Feeling fear is not a sign of weakness but rather a sign of humanness.
.
.
Humans (including yourself) will experience a myriad of emotional experiences. This includes fear, anxiety, discomfort, etc. I believe in your ability to redefine your definition of strength (if it needs it). I believe in your ability to validate your strength in living each day fighting against fear and anxiety making your choices. I believe in your ability to do hard things. I believe in YOU! You got this💪
.
.

This is for anyone who needs this reminder today. You can do hard things even when your anxiety, depression, eating disorder, self-critic, self-doubt, perfectionism, etc. is screaming at you that you can’t. You can do hard things even when you don’t want to do them. You can do hard things even when your stomach is churning and your body wants you to escape. You can do hard things even when you don’t feel like you can. You can do hard things. I believe in your ability to do hard things. I believe in YOU!
.
.

Choosing values over fear is not always an easy choice. Sometimes (oftentimes?) it will be “easier" to make a decision based on fear rather than your values. This leads to an immediate feeling of relief; however, that relief is temporary. It also might be coupled with regret, sadness, and demoralization. That fear-based avoidance actually reinforces the scary stimuli leading to a stronger fear association.
.
.
To choose values over fear is such a strength. You may tremble the whole time. You may feel fear coursing through your veins. Part of you may wish you hadn’t said “bring it on” to your anxiety. The situation might not play out the way you had hoped it would, but there is such tremendous benefit to making decisions based on values. This is your life to live; not fear’s.
.
.
I believe in your ability to do hard things. I believe in your ability to do scary things. I believe in your ability to walk towards your fear and resist retreating. I believe in you SO much! You got this💪
.
.

Oo this one can be so challenging! You might struggle at times with both saying “no” and holding to that boundary for fear of someone being upset or mad. To that I say, your ability and right to have boundaries is not contingent on another’s reaction to those boundaries. You get to have boundaries and say no regardless of the response of the individual on the receiving end of your boundaries. If they get upset, that’s on them- not you.
.
.
I believe in your ability to do hard things. I believe in your ability to set and hold to (and reinforce when needed) firm boundaries. I believe in your ability to use “no” as a complete sentence. I believe in YOU! You got this💪
.
.

Watch out for this trap! You might feel like it will be helpful to check just one more time (how many times have you heard that phrase, right?!) with the internet, OCD books, your therapist, your family, etc. that what you are worried about/what you are currently struggling with is really OCD, but this can be another tricky compulsion. Even though it may make us feel temporary “relief”, we know compulsions make OCD worse/stronger. We know that this reassurance seeking won’t help us in the long run.
.
.
I believe in your ability to resist compulsions. I believe in your ability to embrace uncertainty even when it feels so wrong to do so. I believe in your ability to do hard things. I believe in YOU! You got this! 💪
.
.

You might experience an upsetting intrusive thought while engaging in an intimate/personal act (e.g., going to the bathroom, putting on/adjusting your underwear, using a tampon, kissing, having sex, etc.) OCD may then tell you this means something about you. This is another lie.
.
.
Having an intrusive thought at any point during your day means nothing about you. It may feel like it does, but keep in mind that feeling this way does not make it true. Feelings aren’t facts.👍
.
.
I believe in you and your ability to resist OCD’s lies. I believe in your ability to do very hard things. I believe in you SO SO much! You got this💪

Thoughts do not hold moral value. Your OCD may say they do and that you are “bad” for having a “bad” thought. This is one of OCD’s many lies. We can resist buying into this lie and see thoughts as what they are- a moment(s) of our brain noticing something. We can engage with our thoughts like clouds passing by (which they will do if we can resist that urge to latch onto them). This can be SO hard but you can do hard things. I believe in YOU! You got this💪
.
.

This can be SO hard! We may feel that dreaded pit in our stomach, that shakiness in our limbs, and the sweatiness in our palms. We can accept these with non- judgment as part of our internal experience. We can make decisions based on our values. We can run, walk, skip, crawl (whatever mode you choose) towards our anxiety instead of away from it. When we move towards our fear instead of away from it, we reinforce that we can do hard things. We may emerge from the task exhausted and disheveled but we will emerge nonetheless.
.
.
I SO believe in you! I believe in your courage. I believe in your strength. I believe in your compassion. I believe in your ability to do hard things. You got this!
.

Keep an eye out for getting caught up in the content of your intrusive thoughts. The content is meaningless. There is really no limit to what the human brain can create and this can lead to some really creative/disturbing/odd/interesting thoughts. Good thing the content is meaningless!
.
.
It can be so difficult to step outside of the content and see the intrusions for what they truly are. They are thoughts passing by which don’t deserve to be latched onto. The reason why we can get so wrapped up in the content is because OCD knows how to really get us. OCD goes after what we care about (safety, our family, certainty, health, comfort, etc.) and mixes it with the worst thing. This creates that perfect storm where we can fall into the content and the urge to ritualize presents itself.
.
.
I believe in your ability to step outside of the content. I believe in your ability to allow your intrusive thoughts to hang out beside you as long as they want, without giving them food. I believe in your ability to do these hard things! I believe in you! You got this💪
.
.

I’ve posted this sentiment before and I’m sure I’ll post it again sometime. That’s how important I believe this message is.
.
.
Yes, brains are awesome but they are not infallible! We can get into a difficult spot if we take everything our brains tell us as automatic fact. Some of our thoughts are factual, but the reason these thoughts would be fact is because there’s actual evidence to back them up (evidence is not “because I thought it”).
.
.
I believe in your ability to not believe everything you think. Our brains will tell us loads of things that aren’t true. Thoughts are able to be challenged. You can do these hard things! I believe in you. You got this!💪
.

Those pesky “what ifs?” can be so tempting to dig into and try to figure out and/or solve. The thing is, these tend to be unanswerable questions. We can’t solve those future-based “what ifs?” in this moment. Even if a "what if?" is for one hour in the future, it’s still the future. In fact, if we take a step back, we may even see that we don’t need to answer these questions. We can accept uncertainty. We can also accept the discomfort associated with doubt. We can do things without certainty in how they will go. We can do hard things! I believe in you. You got this!💪
.

.
.

What would you do differently if you fully believed in yourself and what you were going for?

Me: “Alexa, what am I supposed to be doing with my life?” Alexa: “Hmm, I don’t know that”
.
Just a general rule of thumb...if Alexa doesn’t know, you’re off the hook! Haha!🤷🏼‍♀️
.
Where are you going to college? What will you study? What are you going to do after you graduate? When are you getting married? Are you going to have any children? Are you just going to be a stay at home mom/dad (said in a condescending tone)? on and on until forever...
.
Repeat after me: “I DON’T KNOW,” end of sentence. I know, it feels so weird...because not knowing means we’re incompetent and unprepared, am I right? Plot twist: we’re all pretty unprepared for life, so why are we trying to play it off like we’ve got it all together?
.
“I don’t know:” perfectly good enough answer! Use it, lean in to it, and bask in the glory of making choices whenever YOU want to, not when you’re “supposed” to.
.
Do you ever feel the pressure to have all the answers? Can I get a 🙋‍♀️
.
.
.

I’ve never known what it’s like to not feel some sort of extreme emotion—and for so long I felt weak because of it. I swallowed my emotions and suppressed my empathetic soul which dimmed my light day by day. Then the darkness woke me up.
.
The more I spoke my truth, the more power I felt. I stopped punishing myself for feeling differently than others. I want the same for you. Don’t ever be ashamed of the way you were made. You are beautiful. You are fearless.
.

I’m sad that the day came where this post was ever necessary and to try and avoid any controversy I am going to put a TW on this post: 
Last night everything got too much. Something clicked and after a long time of fighting every suicidal thought or urge I had, I just couldn’t fight it anymore. I took an overdose last night. The world was not on my side and everything got too much for me. The good news is is that I’m safe, I’m home and hopefully the mental health team I’ve been discharged to will actually start to do something. However, and let this be a lesson to you all, I massively regret my decision to do something of the sort - I was overwhelmed and quite honestly done fighting with all my might everyday. Yes this is a huge setback and yes an all time low but I’m trying to turn it around and find the positives in what was a horrific experience. I’m safe, I’m at home (which I’m grateful for as there was potential of being put on a psych ward), I’m going to start (hopefully) getting the help I need, I’m confident that next time I will speak to my parents before I get to this point and I’m hoping it will be the start of turning my life around for the better. I’m sorry if I’ve let anyone down or disappointed anyone, life just got too much for me but please know that I’m in a more positive mindset this morning and I feel ready to start fighting once again and beat these stupid illnesses! I can do this. I want to thank my incredible (understatement) friends who were there for me last night - I don’t know what I would do without you. Anyway I’m safe and that’s what matters. Keep fighting everyone and if anyone has any questions just drop me a message and I’ll try my best to answer honestly. Lots of love to you all and keep fighting ~ Abbi xxx #depression #ocd #stopthestigma

A lot of the time I can’t find the right words to describe depression. It’s exhausting it’s draining it’s upsetting. It feels like the life is being sucked out of you and the small amount of energy you have takes all your effort to use. I’m sad to say that a lot of my smiles are forced at the moment - and when you’re depressed it really does take all your effort to smile. A lot of the time it feels like the world is crumbling around you and even getting out of bed in the morning is a task that pretty much hoovers up all your energy. Depression is real and depression sucks! BUT: things will get better, there will be happy times and you will continue to make amazing memories. Use the people around you as motivation to get better and live a happier life. Don’t let depression win all the time (sometimes is fine) but not all the time. Keep fighting everyone - you can do this!! Xxx #depression #ocd #stopthestigma

Please read: if someone were to see me looking like this I.e. in my pjs in the mid afternoon with a blanket wrapped around myself, they would probably ask if I was unwell. With the absence of a cold or the flu or anything of the sort I would probably automatically answer ‘no’. But in reality the answer is yes. Yes I am unwell! Just not physically. Today my depression is getting the better of me, my mental illness is dominating so yes I am unwell/not feeling very well/ill. But I would never openly answer yes to that question in reference to my mental health. It’s a difficult one because answering yes to that question opens up a whole new conversation with the person asking the question but it would be the truth. Mental illness is still an illness and I think, although resilience and fight is obviously needed, we should still treat it like it’s an illness simply because that’s what it is. I don’t know - what are everyone else’s thoughts? Hope you’re all ok and keep fighting everyone😁😁 #ocd #stopthestigma

“And even though it’s hard and I may struggle through it all, you may see me struggle... but you will NEVER see me fall” ~~~ I’m sure I’ve used this quote before but I think it’s so important!! This trip has been amazing, fabulous, fun, inspiring, beautiful and I’m only half way through it. Buttttt this does not come at all with ease. The anxiety, ocd and depression are still there and they still are making me battle every second of every day and that does prove to be difficult. I think the hardest thing is the exhaustion that this causes as I’ve got to fight through every day but I also have to fight the tiredness that comes with battling ocd and depression. It’s hard to be having a perfectly normal fun day but feel so unbelievably low for no reason - that is frustrating beyond belief. It’s also hard to repeat things a million times in your head and go over and over the same thing until it feels right whilst trying to maintain a “normal” outwards persona. But these are the challenges I’ve been given and though I may struggle through it at times, it does not stop me from living my life and doing what I want to do!! That is the most important thing, do what you want to do - you only live once and there is no point in being unhappy because someone or something else is controlling your life. No matter how bad your mental illness is, you are still in there somewhere and let that bit be the bit that takes control. It’s ok to struggle but just don’t fall, so hold on tight and enjoy the ride!! Cheers🍻 #ocd #stopthestigma

Currently got WiFi on a plane 35000 feet in the air. I GOT ON THE PLANE!! I never thought I could do this on my own and this is one huge massive fighting Friday but also one huge massive step in the right direction. OCD and depression have been well and truly trampled on. It’s not been easy but I’m on the plane and that’s what matters!! 4 hours to go💖💖 #fightingfriday #ocd #stopthestigma

It’s a sad and difficult reality for a lot of people that OCD and mental illness makes you miss out on things you want to do. But it’s also true that you don’t have to let mental illness stop you from having fun altogether. Yes there will be bumps in the road, some things will go right and some very wrong but as long as you always pick yourself back up and force a smile life will never be all negative. You can all do it xxx #ocd #stopthestigma

First of all we’re England insane or were they insane? Secondly -on Friday I fly to Hong Kong ON MY OWN!! I’m bricking it😱😱 My OCD makes it very difficult to do things on my own because of touching stuff and anxiety makes me feel really sick so it’s always easier to be with others. But... I think I’m ready for this. I’m ready to take this step and I know that this will be an enormous achievement for me. I’m so so anxious about it and it doesn’t really seem real but I know it will be fine and I CAN DO IT! I fully back myself with this I know I can do this. Hopefully it will be an amazing week in Hong Kong and Japan and I will be absolutely fine. I will keep yall updated but just wanted to take the time to say DONT LET MENTAL ILLNESS STOP YOU DOING WHAT YOU WANT TO DO! No matter how daunting and scary it might be - you can do it if you really really push yourself❤️❤️ love you all - keep fighting xxx #ocd #stopthestigma

Last ever tennis tournament for our school and not really sure how I feel. It’s a sad time and I’m not good with change but I’m pushing on through and trying my absolute best. I’ve been so good with my ocd today - haven’t washed my hands at all (but haven’t been to loo obvs) and still touching my phone📱 I’m proud of myself for how well I’ve been doing considering the circumstances but im v nervous about having to socialise at the leavers ball and get through speech day and stuff. But I will go in with a PMA and it will be fine. Pushing on through and a day of tennis and sunshine has been great for the mood - along with my super tennis partner💖💖 keep fighting everyone #ocd #stopthestigma 🎾 #bummertheyareoutforsummer #etontennis #youcantcensormyskin

Do you want to know what the greatest roadblock is for a health anxiety sufferer on their road to freedom? I call it the standing guard cycle. This cycle presupposes that if a health anxiety sufferer stands guard at the doorway of their body throughout each and every moment of their life, and reacts instinctively and fearfully to anything that may seem ‘abnormal’ to them in their body, they stay in the safe zone. The safe zone is to be able to maintain this run of survival they have going, to hope for change but to run the same mental, emotional habits from day to day due to the formula that safety lies within worry, and safety lies within what’s been familiar.
.
Standing guard means to tense up the body, this is something the health anxiety sufferer doesn’t recognize though because they are solely concerned about the impulsive reaction to what they view as an abnormal feeling in the body. By standing guard though we tense up the body and internal organs causing an even greater amount of misinterpretations to any external stimuli that shows up. A tense body picks up on other peoples language that may touch on the topic of illness instantly. A tense body will become 100 times more stimulated to sound, smell, and taste.
.
Standing guard keeps the anxious identity in tact, in fact strengthening it by the day. The longer a paradigm, or a set of habits have been in place, the more difficult it becomes to break. Why would your system begin seeing the sensations and the world in a whole different light? It kept you alive up to now didn’t it? It did, but it sucks to live by standing guard constantly. If the subconscious mind/body wants to stand guard, that fine, that’s it’s job anyway which is to keep you safe and to keep you happy. But the conscious mind doesn’t have to join in. The conscious mind upon recognIzing a lengthy period of standing guard can break free through the power of mindfulness and begin partaking in a new viewpoint over the sensation it feels. #MoreThanAnxiety
.

What you feel comes down to the connections you’ve made that determine whether something is good, bad, safe, unsafe, true, untrue etc. To believe that our feelings are truth and to consistently act in harmony with them means we no longer utilize our strength in thinking, but rely on our feelings to guide us slowly. This efficient brain and body connection wants nothing more than for you to keep your life moving forward on repeat, playing out the same actions and thoughts day by day. But in truth this limits what we’re capable of experiencing and also keeps us stuck living as we did when we were kids.
.
Life begins to change rapidly when you begin choosing your responses rather than letting your emotions do it for you. There is nothing more satisfying than to defy your fears and limits through action and inaction that opposes what your automatic system believes is truth. Over time this takes you out of living by the truths of your childhood and into the process of creation. You can create an inner environment that is pleasant over chaotic. But you must choose this path first, and next you must sacrifice what needs to be sacrificed along this journey to healing. When you’re ready I’ll be here to guide you. ❤️
.

Anxiety is a physical response, and yet it cannot be generated without certain constructed internal representations of possible future events.
.
In anticipating future challenges, we estimate the significance of the challenge, and the strength of our resources to respond to that challenge.
.
Anxiety sufferers comments about life and their own self are based on a "permanent pervasive style" of explanation (this is the way I and other things are, everything is like this, and it always will be).
.
Generally the depressed person has given up trying to avoid the kind of pain that the anxious person is running from.
.
3 Steps to get started towards healing anxiety:
.
1. Understand your situation - How did you get to where you are today?
2. Decide what you want (in sensory based language)
3. Commit to the path (adaptive healing strategies)
.

Nice post @iamdaliasmith
Going down these traumatic roads also gives us an advantage. We know the way back! Let’s Press rewind 🎞.
Someone’s got to do it! Who’s with me ? 💪🏾 Good Morning Kings and Queens 👸🏾 🤴🏾
Let’s get healthy the RIGHT way! There is a difference, and understanding the impacting factors will guide you in the right direction.
Do any of these sound familiar ? Let’s start connecting the dots. Word of the Day AWARENESS! Great Post @dlcanxietysupport
Purpose Driven 🤔💭
Embrace the Good in your life. The negative things get enough energy. Word of the day SABOTAGE! Identify where it’s effecting you, and minimize.
Allow what is needed to flow naturally. No force, no influence, and reasoning from society. A clear Mind 🧠 thinks best 💭
Pick your head Up Queens 👸🏾 and if it’s already up. Pick it up HIGHER 👑
Morning Lessons! Let everyone grow at their own pace. It works better when it’s natural and unforced.
Lets talk about ANXIETY! Here’s an example from personal experience. Hope it helps 🤕

I WISH!!! I’ll Put it right on the dresser like dentures 🧠. But in the mean time, we have to find ways calm or pace ourself, so mentally we aren’t always on the GO. The garbage man comes every 4 days in my town, are you taking out the trash?  @psychiatricmind

ThrowBack to Year 1 of the practice. Boy has time flew. The growth from stepping out on a limb to being recognized as one of the most affective mental health agencies in my community. What a return I’ve gotten by blessing others.
It will come a time when there is no where else to run 🏃. That only leaves one option ..... FIGHT!!!
Exploit your talents. They might be Unique. Happy Friday! It’s the last few months before 2020, What you gone do with it!  #community
This is surely easier said then done , but something that will change how you feel on a daily basis. Dismissing negative thoughts is a SKILL! Develop it 🙏🏾
Once we become aware of our problems, we can’t procrastinate on something as delicate as our MENTAL HEALTH. Catch it early, it’s called PREVENTION!!! G👀D Morning Kings and Queens Happy Sunday🤴🏾 👸🏾
