// 𝙍𝙀𝘿. The experiment. //⁣
New addition to my A.M. routine.⁣
-⁣
At the @thearkeventspace launch last month,⁣
I sat beside a #Superbabe with #flawless skin (literally!)
⁣
As 2 curious aquaphobic “biohackers”,⁣
we instantly clicked & spent the rest of the night talking⁣ about nutrigenomics, bioresonace tech, flotation tanks,⁣ MCT/fat burning hacks & red/NIR light therapy.⁣
⁣
I told her that after reading @dave.asprey’s book⁣
“𝘏𝘦𝘢𝘥 𝘚𝘵𝘳𝘰𝘯𝘨” a year ago; I’d been looking for a⁣
legit/affordable home device for red/NIR light treatment⁣ but still no luck finding an independently verified one⁣ with medical grade power that I was⁣
100% comfortable purchasing.⁣
⁣
She then said (simplified sentence),⁣
“𝐈’𝐯𝐞 𝐛𝐞𝐞𝐧 𝐮𝐬𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐨𝐧𝐞! 𝐀𝐧𝐝 𝐢𝐭’𝐬 𝐞𝐟𝐟𝐞𝐜𝐭𝐢𝐯𝐞!”⁣
⁣
So we exchanged numbers & she sent me⁣
Mark Sloan’s book about red light therapy as⁣
a natural treatment for acne, pain, fat loss⁣
& other remarkable healing benefits.⁣
⁣
While Camila Mendes, Bella Hadid & other⁣
Celebs/health experts use red light therapy for⁣
various reasons, it’s not a cure for diseases. But⁣
⁣
𝐎𝐩𝐭𝐢𝐦𝐢𝐬𝐞𝐝 𝐜𝐞𝐥𝐥𝐮𝐥𝐚𝐫 𝐟𝐮𝐧𝐜𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧 = 𝘽𝙤𝙙𝙮 𝙧𝙚𝙥𝙖𝙞𝙧𝙨 𝙞𝙩𝙨𝙚𝙡𝙛 𝙛𝙖𝙨𝙩𝙚𝙧.⁣
The result = natural collagen production, skin clarity;⁣ better sexual, thyroid & brain function, etc. ⁣
⁣
@__bryanl (dusted off his camera to shoot this)
& I are⁣ saving up for a life-size panel so we can⁣
full-body experiment it on my current state of health.⁣ But for now, we got what @lezannc recommended⁣
for start off with, on-the-go. Yay.👏🏼❤️⁣
⁣
Thanks a bunch Lez & @jluv7⁣
(we wouldn’t have met if it weren’t for you!🥰).⁣
⁣

but we can take this conversation to InstaStories,⁣
where you can go ahead, ask me anything & will⁣
do my best to answer as many within the next 24hrs.⁣
⁣
On the move until Oct,⁣
but will update whenever possible.⁣

While there has been more attention paid to prenatal and postpartum depression and anxiety recently, we have far to go to learn about this crisis and help protect women. •

We need to continue to talk about it, study it, research it, and identify & treat women at risk. •

Usually, trying to "push away" upsetting images only makes them worse. Here's a brain hack: when you or your child are bothered by intrusive images left behind from a movie, nightmare, or risky click on the internet, visualize (or draw!) a story that transforms the scary thing into something not-so-scary. .
.
. ✋🛑 Intrusive images from traumatic experiences are a bit wilder of a beast to tame. 🐯 This method may or may not help manage symptoms, but processing the experience with a trauma-informed therapist is best. 
#🧠 #brainhack #psychology #weekendvibes #scarythoughts #empathproblems #highlysensitiveperson #parentinghacks #motherhoodrising

Ty 🙏❤️ @scarymommy and #2020mom for raising this important and underreported issue •
•
“September is National Suicide Prevention Month, so there is no better time to educate ourselves about how to personally identify, support and help those struggling with postpartum stress and depression — which can sometimes be so subtle even those closest to them don’t notice. “Even loving partners and loved ones can easily miss signs that a woman is experiencing high levels of distress because postpartum women go to great lengths to present themselves as if they are in control and feeling good,” Karen Kleiman, author and founder of The Postpartum Stress Center, LLC on behalf of 2020 Mom, tells Scary Mommy. Even more, is that postpartum depression doesn’t have a one-size-fits-all look to it.

For example, a mom who isolates herself, withdraws from friends or family, becomes quiet or shuts down, may not appear to be as distressed as a mom who is experiencing panic attacks and saying she can’t stand the way she feels. However, “both moms are suffering, but presenting their distress differently,” she points out. Kleiman suggests looking your loved one straight in the eye and asking her how she is feeling. Then, look her in the eyes and ask her again.”
•

Make sure you let someone you trust know how you are feeling. ❤️ #speakthesecret

Anxiety during pregnancy and the postpartum period can play tricks with your head and make you believe you are the only one who is suffering. It can bias your perceptions and drag you toward darker thoughts. Try to check yourself by practicing self-compassion and mindful cognitive corrections, such as: "It's okay. I'm okay. Everything is fine." Say it outloud. Remind yourself that you might be misinterpreting what you are observing or feeling. Allow the anxiety to be present, but don't empower it by paying too much attention to it. Distract your brain. Breathe. Be good to yourself. •

hola semuaaa! siapa kangen akuuu😋😋 kali ini aku mau rekomendasiin kalian sebuah brushpen. brushpen ini bener bener unik banget si. finetip nya ituloo bisa dibuat ngebrush jugaa. hasilnya bisa kalian liat di yang quotes ya! (lebih lanjutnya di highlight) buruan cek deh!!
hai semuanyaa maaf banget aku se-ja-rang itu on nyaaa😭😭 btw, ini aku nge re-write catetan lama ku😋 karena blm ada materi kuliah. kalian setuju ga kalo next ny aku gapake watercolor lagi HEHEHEHEH

🖍textliner 38 pastel🖍
hai semuanyaaa! maaf banget ni aku jarang aktif upload sg. lagi ospek bertahap tahap ga selesai selesai (ﾉД`) kali ini aku mau rekomendasiin kalian semacam highlighter gitu yang warnanya tuh kalem parahh(ada 6 macam warna). gabikin sakit mata sama sekali. yaitu Faber-Castell Textliner 38 Pastel. 
textliner ini tuh bisa dipake buat ngegaris dengan 2 macam ketebalan (3,5mm dengan ujung yang tebal dan 1mm dengan ujung yang runcing). bentuk dari textliner ini ramping, jadi gabakal ngehabisin space di pencase kalian.

✒️Faber-Castell Fineliner🖋
Jadi ceritanya, aku kan cuma punya 12 warna pen yang berbeda. Pastinya kurang dong, ya kaan. Nah kebetulan banget nih aku ada faber-castell fineliner. 
Fineliner ini bener bener usefull parah sih. Karena tipnya kan kecil ya, mirip mirip pen normal. Jadinya bisa dipake buat nulis, nggambar detail, atau menghias catetan kalian.

Faber-castell menyediakan 30 macam warna untuk fineliner ini. Yang pasti tintanya tebel dan warna nya cerah cerah💛. Dan bonusnya adalaah.. Si fineliner ini tuh washable ink. Jadi kalo semisal kalian lagi nulis, terus ga sengaja kecoret di baju kalian. Itu tinggal dicuci. Udah bisa ilang🤩

Recommended banget lah pastinyaa

🖊faber-castell air gel🖊
hai semuanyaaa! jadi, aku punya pen baru yang bakalan jadi favorite pen aku banget sih ini😭👌🏼 namanya faber-castell air gel. pen ini tuh bener bener seenak itu, alus pisan😂

pen ini tersedia dua ketebalan nip, yaitu 0.5mm dan 0.7mm. cocok cocokan ama kaliannya si. tintanya ituloohh top parah! bener bener halus dan lancar banget di kertas. 
btw, tinta air gel ini bener bener cepet kering loh, jadi kalo semisal mau nge highlight bisa langsung tanpa nunggu lama🤘🏼. untuk kenyamanan ditangan sii, top juga lah pastinya. karena dia tuh ada soft gripnya gitu, gabakal bikin tangan kalian sakit atau kadang mbekas gitu kalo kelamaan nulis. 
recommended parah deh pokoknya😋✨

🎒student pack🎒
super recommended buat kalian para pelajar yang suka bawa barang barang simple tapi isinya berguna semua! desain pencase yang super simple ini eksklusif dari Jerman🤩🇩🇪 ma fav country🤪

🎒1 Mechanical Pencil 1328
🎒1 Dust Free Eraser

It’s a sad day but I’m letting you guys know. I’m downsizing and rehoming some of my Axolotls to try and help with Hiccup’s bills. You can still donate to his GoFundMe at the link in my bio.
Hiccup has had a good day again. He still hates taking his meds. 😂 I’m still hoping to receive more donations. I still have a lot to pay off. Thank you to those who have donated so far. ❤️

Tried to get to some normality today at @oak_park_natural_pet_and_fish after the chaos of last week with Hiccup. (link to donate to his medical bills is in my bio) So here is some pictures of some beautiful fish. I love the Flame Angel! Maybe one day I’ll have a salt water tank... But for now I’ll just enjoy the sights.

Hiccup and I are both happy this seems to be simmering down. We’ve both been sleeping off and on since about 5pm. No complaints here though. I think we are equally as exhausted. I could still really use donations for his vet bills though. If you can donate even $1 it would help us greatly. Link is in my bio.

He came home today! He is VERY tired of you can’t tell. We haven’t gotten a clear explication on what happened but this ER vet is thinking it was a series of medications for the URI that he was slightly allergic to. These medications caused an upset in his stomach making everything worse. We are hoping the whole ordeal is over. If all goes well he will need to visit his primary 1 more time next week to get another complete blood test to make sure all his levels are back to normal. He is now down to 3 medications and his URI appears to have cleared up. Not it’s just getting his stomach settled and keeping him from eating too much, too fast.

Visited the patient today. He was very happy to see me. He was purring and was nothing but cuddles. He will hopefully be coming home tomorrow. His X-Rays today did show some abnormalities in his intestines and their ability to move things along. They are going to do an ultrasound tomorrow to see if they can clearly see the issues. So far I’m not entirely sure what is going on. I thought we had a diagnosis but it seems we are back to square 1 again. Hopefully tomorrow we will have some answers. I appreciate everyone who has donated to the GoFundMe the last few days. I am blown away by how kind everyone is. With that being said, we still have a ways to go. You can donate through the link in my bio.

I’ve been sleeping much of today so far... I’m burnt out. But I wanted to make a post to thank everyone who has donated or does donate. I’m blown away by your generosity and I honestly can’t believe you’ve raised this amount of money in just a couple of days. Hiccup and I feel very loved. 😭❤️ The link to donate is in my bio.

Hiccup is back in the ER for an overnight stay. After vomiting 4 times this evening I decided it was in his best interest to go to the ER since his nausea medications were not working and the fear of some sort of bowel obstruction is all I can think about, even though it’s supposedly ruled out. I don’t know much right now other than what the bill is going to be when I pick him up tomorrow or Monday. I’m honestly at a loss for words right now. I’m exhausted physically, emotionally and financially at this point. I could really use any donations at this point since the financial aspect of this is going beyond what I ever thought it would be... Even a $1 helps. The link for his gofundme is in my bio.

Hiccup Update: Overall he was good today. He got more meds and some fluids as well. He did vomit a few times this evening but after being given another dose of nausea medication he seems to be okay. He’s sleeping a lot but is still interested in food and is drinking water. He’s on 4 different medications as of right now. One for nausea, one for acid buildup, an antibiotic, and an appetite stimulant. I can tell he is happy to be home. Tomorrow will be his first day without needing to see his vet. He is set to see his vet for a followup on Monday, which will hopefully be his last visit. The bills are really adding up... Feel free to donate to his gofundme in my bio.

I meant to debut my new boy last week before all this Hiccup madness but got distracted for obvious reasons. This is Kevin and also my first attempt at a planted tank. I’m really excited about this but didn’t want to cloud Hiccup’s emergency with a new pet. I did get him before everything that happened with Hiccup though. Just so people don’t get grumpy. I finally finished his tank today. 😄 Hiccup is doing well for those still worried. I’ll do a full update on Hiccup later today.

Hiccup Update: Sick boy is home for the weekend! He ate some of his fancy food I got from work right away when we got home which made me very happy. After a long talk with his vet this evening we have concluded that the Upper Respiratory Infection and the GI tract infection were unrelated and that Hiccup most likely has an underlying chronic disease (like feline herpes). So when the URI hit him, his immune system went haywire, causing a secondary infection in the GI tract. This made for a very sick and miserable Baby Munch. He is now on about 5 different medications for the weekend but is much more bright eyed and alert than he was this morning. His feisty personality it back and he is turning back into his cuddle bug self. We still aren’t out of the woods yet, and he will be returning to his primary for another check up on Monday. But he has improved leaps and bounds since Tuesday. I want to thank everyone for the outpouring of love and support and a special thank you to those who have donated to his medical bills in the last 24 hours. The donations are helping ease the stress. You can donate to his GoFundMe at the link in my bio. ❤️

Hiccup is spending the day with his primary vet again on IV fluids. He’ll be getting another ultrasound this morning to make sure everything is moving along as well. Overall he seemed more himself today. He was purring this morning, asking for snuggles and being a little feisty with his vet as well. Both very Hiccup things to do! I’ll give more updates later today when I know more. The link to donate is in my bio. Thank you to those who have already. Hiccup and I appreciate and thank you for your generosity and positive vibes.

Hello friends....Hiccup’s bills have put quite a lot on my emergency credit card this week so I am allowing donations through gofundme to help ease the pressure... Feel free to donate if you’d like but never feel like you have to. As I stated when Remi was sick, I will be able to pay it off eventually without a problem. The link to donate is in my Instagram bio. Thank you to everyone for the kind words and positive vibes. We all appreciate it and they have made me feel much better through all this.

Hiccup went back to the vet today. He still wasn’t eating and was even more lethargic and not himself this morning so I decided to take him to his primary vet. They decided to run an ultrasound and found massive fluid build up in his stomach, ulcers in the back of his throat, and a GI tract that was very irritated. They did blood tests, which the ER apparently should have done to begin with, and ruled out kidney failure and pancreatitis but did see his white blood cells were also through the roof meaning he’s fighting quite an infection. I decided to leave him in the care of his vet for the day so he could get the care he deserves. He spent 7 hours there today, but is home again for the night. After a large dose of fluids (which apparently the ER never gave him on Tuesday,) more antibiotics and some meds for the fluid buildup in his stomach. Her just got home and I can report he ate a few nibbles of food right when he got home. He’s more alert now and was walking around saying hi to all the other kitties. He is currently resting in his carrier. It’s been a long day for sure. He has an IV catheter in for the night and will be going back to the vet first thing tomorrow for another ultrasound.

Update: Hiccup got to come home this morning. He’s still very lethargic and is at grump level 11 right now. He’s on 2 medications to help with pain and nausea. He is currently hiding under my bed. He hasn’t eaten yet, so I’m going to try and tempt him with some wet food after work tonight. We are both exhausted right now. So naps all around.

So I have to spend my night without my Baby Munch aka Hiccup. He was taken to the ER around 1am for vomiting, nasal discharge, and abdominal discomfort. I took him in thinking I’d come home with him... He is diagnosed with an Upper Respiratory Infection and due to his breed is having a difficult time eating, drinking, and even breathing. He is being kept overnight on oxygen, IV fluids, and IV antibiotics. I feel like an awful owner for not catching this sooner... You all know I would do anything for my pets. It was a tearful drive home without him tonight. I’ll be picking him up in the morning to transfer him to his primary vet.
Apple picking with my friends today! Love days like this. ❤️

My ep club lullabies has been out for a little over a month, and I want to share with you about the artwork that inspired the last song, yoko's tree.
.
.
. ”Wish Tree is an ongoing art installation series by Japanese artist Yoko Ono, started sometime after 1981, in which a tree native to a site is planted under her direction. Viewers are usually invited to tie a written wish to the tree except during the winter months when a tree can be more vulnerable.
.
.
.
Her 1996 Wish Piece had the following instructions:
.
.
Make a wish. Write it down on a piece of paper. Fold it and tie it around a branch of a Wish Tree. Ask your friends to do the same. Keep wishing. Until the branches are covered with wishes.
.
.
.
To honor wish writers' privacy, Ono claims she does not read the wishes, and collects them all to be buried at the base of the Imagine Peace Tower on Viðey Island in Kollafjörður Bay in Iceland. To date over 1 million wishes have been buried beneath the tower.
.
.
She has also said: 
As a child in Japan, I used to go to a temple and write out a wish on a piece of thin paper and tie it around the branch of a tree. Trees in temple courtyards were always filled with people's wish knots, which looked like white flowers blossoming from afar.” .
.
.
Yoko ono is one of my favorite artists and has a great warm place in my heart. Hope you will enjoy ”yoko’s tree”, (and my not so secret wish).
.
.
.
.
.
.
